request.description:
## **Overview:**

This documentation provides details on how to sign up a user with his/her credentials.

**Endpoint:** `/api/signup`  
**Method:** `post`

## Request Headers:

- **name**: (string) The name of the user.
    
- **username** (string) The username of the user. Need to check against already used usernames.
    
- **email**: (string) The email address of the user.
- **password**: (string) The password associated with the email.
    

## Response

The endpoint responds with a JSON object containing a success/error message accordingly.

## **End Point Example :**

POST `/api/signup`  
Body:

name: user

username: user123  
email: [user@example.com](https://mailto:user@example.com)  
password: mysecretpassword

## **Overview:**

This documentation provides details on how to authenticate and obtain a token from the login endpoint. The endpoint accepts user credentials in the form of email and password and returns a token upon successful authentication.

**Endpoint:** `/api/login`  
**Method:** `get`

## Request Body:

- **userID**: (string) The email address or user name of the user.
    
- **password**: (string) The password associated with the email.
    

## Response

The endpoint responds with a JSON object containing a token upon successful authentication.

## **End Point Example :**

GET `/api/login`  
Body:  
email: [user@example.com](https://mailto:user@example.com)  
password: mysecretpassword

StartFragment

## **Overview:**

This documentation provides details on how to assign role to a user. By default, everyone is admin on their own account. The child users can be upgraded to admin roles with this API. If child user doesn't exist, send appropriate response with error.

**Endpoint:** `/api/role`

**Method:** `GET`

## Request Headers:

- **email**: (string) The email address of the child user.
    
- **role**: (string) The role to be assigned - "admin"/"std_user".
    

## Response

The endpoint responds with a JSON object containing a message for successful role assignment.

## **End Point Example :**

POST `/api/role-assign`  
Headers:  
token:

Body:

email:

role: "admin"/"std_user"

EndFragment

## **Overview:**

This API endpoint provides auto-suggestions based on the query provided. It's designed to assist users in finding relevant suggestions based on their input.

**Endpoint:** `/api/autoSuggest`  
**Method:** `POST`

## Parameters:

- **q** (required): The query string for which auto-suggestions are requested. This parameter should be URL encoded.
    

## **End Point Example :**

POST `{{url}}:{{port}}api/autoSuggest?q=hero`

response.name: Updated Auto Complete

request.description:
## Overview

This API endpoint performs a fuzzy search based on the provided query string, returning relevant results that match closely to the query.

**Endpoint:** `/api/fuzzySearch`  
**Method:** `POST`

## Parameters:

- **q** (required): StartFragmentThe query string for which fuzzy search results are requested. This parameter should be URL encoded.EndFragment
    

## **End Point Example :**

POST `{{url}}:{{port}}/api/fuzzySearch?q=thoo`

request.description:
## **Overview:**

The \`availableUser\` endpoint allows clients to check the availability of an email address and username in the system. It verifies if the provided email or username is already associated with an existing user account.

**Method :**

GET `api/availableUser`  
  

**Body Parameters:**

| Parameter | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| email | string | The email address to check for availability. |
| username | string | The username to check for availability. |

## Response

### Success Response

#### Status Code: 200 OK

#### Status Code: 400 Bad Request

- **Content:** `{ "error": "Email or username already in use" }`

This api endpoint will be called when user clicks on play button to watch any movie.

movieId and token are sent in body.

User watch history will be stored in database and if some movie is already watched, date is updated to latest.

This api endpoint taken a token and searches all the recent movies searched by user.

**Sort/ order** : Latest movies are sent first.

**Limit** : At present latest 10 movies are sent.

**Result** : get all information of moveis added by api/addRecentMovies for a particular user.
